[color=red][size=18]Spec Racer Ford Challenge Series @ [b] Road Atlanta Short[/b]
Week 6 of 12 - 2017 Season 1 [/size][/color]
Race Distance: [b]20 laps[/b], approximately 25 minutes
World Record lap time (qualifying): [b]1:05.545[/b] by Christian Challiner
(n.b. random/dynamic weather impacts lap times greatly)

Week 6 sees the first of our two visits to Road Atlanta this season. This time we are using the short layout. Road Atlanta is another american racetrack with a long and storied history of top-flight racing - including the Petit Le Mans endurance races. The racing is excellent and very intense on this short layout. However, there are a couple of tricky/blind corners so it's important to take it easy at first until you have a good feel for the track.

Target "planned" SoF race is usually 20:45 GMT Sunday, immediately following the Weekend Warriors league race.

[img]http://members.iracing.com/jforum/posts/downloadAttach/2363148.page[/img]

